cs.NI, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY 

This paper discusses a switching architecture and scheduling algorithms for efficient packet forwarding and buffer utilization, which are relevant to computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves hardware modifications and memory speedup, which are related to computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The scheduling algorithms and contentions resolution are also related to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY).
